.TH "vc4_set_tiling_ioctl" 9 "vc4_set_tiling_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vc4_set_tiling_ioctl \- Sets the tiling modifier for a BO.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vc4_set_tiling_ioctl
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "data" 12
ioctl argument
.IP "file_priv" 12
DRM file for this fd
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The tiling state of the BO decides the default modifier of an fb if
no specific modifier was set by userspace, and the return value of
\fBvc4_get_tiling_ioctl\fP (so that userspace can treat a BO it
received from dmabuf as the same tiling format as the producer
used).
